misconceptions.inferred_category_name: Missing edge-case handling for empty input (array indexing assumes N>0)
misconceptions.student_thought_process: The student believes there will always be at least one student, so it’s safe to access the last element after sorting.
misconceptions.conceptual_gap: In Java, arrays can have length 0. If N is 0, then computing indexOfTopStudent = numberOfStudents - 1 yields -1, and attempting studentNames[-1] / studentScores[-1] causes an ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException. Correct programs either validate N > 0 before indexing or define behavior for N=0.
